                    <p>A later hand has employed the letters of the alphabet for signing the quires.</p>
                  </item>
                  <item n="2" xml:id="p1addition2">
                    <p>Vowels have been added in <locus from="1" to="61">the first 61 leaves</locus> by a much later hand (<foreign xml:lang="syr">ܰ, ܶ, ܺ, ܳ</foreign>, , or, , , ,). </p><!-- NEED VOWELS -->
                  </item>
                  <item n="3" xml:id="p1addition3">
                    <p>Many lessons have been noted by two later hands, one of which has introduced a marginal division of the Gospels into sections. Of these there are 22 in <ref target="#p1b1">S. Matthew</ref>, 13 in <ref target="#p1b2">S. Mark</ref>, 23 in <ref target="#p1b3">S. Luke</ref>, and 6 in the remaining portion of <ref target="#p1b4">S. John</ref>.</p>
                  </item>
                </list>
